column5: Just curious how the Lac Seul water level compares to passed years at this time of the year??? I have been looking at Ear Falls precipition and it doesn't seem the area is receiving much precip. Pete
Pete: You can check the water level here:http://www.lwcb.ca/ Currently Lac Seul's water level is in great shape...2 1/2 - 3 feet higher than last year at this time. JDP
